150 grams Jasmine Rice
240 grams British Beef Mince
80 grams Sugar Snap Peas
1 sachet(s) Indonesian Style Spice Mix
40 grams Mango Chutney
75 grams Bulgogi Sauce
15 milliliter(s) Soy Sauce
25 grams Salted Peanuts
2 tbsp Tomato Ketchup

Boil a half-full kettle.
Pour it into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat.
Boil the rice, 12-13 mins.
Once cooked, drain. Pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a frying pan on high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince, sugar snaps and Indonesian style spice mix, 5-6 mins. Break up the mince as it cooks.
Drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Stir in the mango chutney, bulgogi, soy and ketchup (see pantry).
Simmer, 1-2 mins.

Share the rice between your bowls.
Spoon over the bulgogi beef and sugar snap peas.
Sprinkle over the peanuts to finish.
Enjoy!